Type 1 license â allows a citizen to own and possess a maximum of two (2) registered firearms;

Type 2 license â allows a citizen to own and possess a maximum of five (5) registered firearms;

Type 3 license â allows a citizen to own and possess a maximum of ten (10) registered firearms;

Type 4 license â allows a citizen to own and possess a maximum of fifteen (15) registered firearms; and

Type 5 license â allows a citizen, who is a certified gun collector, to own and possess more than fifteen (15) registered firearms.

For Types 1 to 5 licenses, a vault or a container secured by lock and key or other security measures for the safekeeping of firearms shall be required.

For Types 3 to 5 licenses, the citizen must comply with the inspection and bond requirements.

